Description


Specifications


Returns & Delivery




Description



The IR Hunter Mark III is the latest enhancement to the IR Hunter product family; the new MKIII continues the success of the MKII models. This new scope incorporates all the existing features of the existing MKII scope and adds a new state-of-the-art stadiametric rangefinder, five reticle patterns, and the ability to save multiple recital set points. With the new 60mm lens, the image quality is much sharper than the previous MKII. Additionally, users will be able to more accurately adjust their reticle position with digital position indicators.
The MKIII-60mm provides 4.5x to 36x magnification. This, combined with the BAE 640×480, 12 micron LWIR thermal core, delivers the best 24/7 image available. Day or night, this scope will help you see the unseen. One of the benefits of the 12 micron technology is that it provides 50% more magnification versus a 17 micron core with the same magnified optic. This feature enables your scope to see farther in a smaller and more compact size. Our 60mm scope provides the same magnification as a 90mm competing scope. Compared to other 17 micro scopes, our new 12 micron MKIII will find targets that other scopes just don’t see. Deep grass or dense tree lines disappear, and the thermal image seen by the MKIII are pronounced and clear. Compare our performance side by side, and your jaw will drop. As one customer put it, “I can’t believe what I haven’t been seeing; if I had not compared my old scope side by side, I would have never known what I was missing!”
The MKIII is feature packed and includes a dual lever LaRue weapon mount, a battery extender, a video/download cable with software, and a flip cap to make recalibration a breeze.




