Very sensitive detector Review by John F 






Quality







Price







Value








                                So far I have found trash at 18 inches (cans), nails 1-2 inches long at 12-18 inches in beach sand and a machete buried in the sand at the beach. So far it is a breeze to operate, still looking for the good stuff.                (Posted on 1/19/2016)


Best priced water detector available Review by Randy K 






Quality







Price







Value








                                I have used this machine for three years and am beyond impressed. I paid for it within 6 months by finding under contract a $20-25k diamond ring. Since that time I have found numerous rings and other types of jewelry, all under contract. On my own time I have dug items as deep as 2 and a half feet deep. All on low mineralized and practically trash less beaches. That is the key, .... if you want depth and hunt in less mineralized, trashy conditions, buy the Sea Hunter.                (Posted on 11/1/2015)


SeaHunterMark II Review by Angel V 






Quality







Price







Value








                                I have owned one of these units for quite some time and have used it mostly in salt water on many Caribbean beaches. I must remark that this unit is one of the best detectors available today. It can discover an earring as deep as 21 inches of wet salty sand. I have used it in many scuba dives and it still is working as the first day out of the box. Your money is well invested, buy with confidence.                (Posted on 8/24/2015)


