Used at the beach and love it! Review by Brownie 

                                                Bought my Sea Hunter in April for use at Myrtle Beach and just returned from vacation where I used it for the first time. I found the detector easy to use and in no time I was digging up all sort of things and found it to be great fun. Did not find any true "treasure", but I did manage to defray the cost of the unit by fifteen cents that I did find. The true treasure was the pleasure I found in hearing the tones and the anticipation of what could be.                (Posted on 8/28/2012)




